<1ST_LINE>u a AM-NudistCampFire     09-06 0221</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Nudist Camp Fire,0225</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Fire At Nudist Camp Sends 300 Fleeing</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Dale for spokesman and spokeswopman is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DEVORE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A propane tank exploded Monday at a nudist
camp, igniting a blaze that injured two people, forced 300 to flee
and destroyed nine buildings and four vehicles, authorities said.
   About 150 of the people are permanent residents of the 53-acre
Tree House Fun Ranch, 50 miles east of downtown Los Angeles, where
the blaze broke out shortly before 3 p.m.
   ``The fire started in the brush and spread to the other areas,''
said San Bernardino County fire Capt. Steve Dale.
   Two of the ranch's homeowners were injured. Rocco Lollo, whose
age was not immediately known, suffered burns over 50 percent of
his body and was to be released after treatment at a hospital, said
Lesley Dale, a county fire department spokeswoman. An unidentified
woman suffered minor injuries, Ms. Dale said.
   The fire burned three acres before being contained at about 4:30
p.m., Dale said. Two homes were destroyed and three were damaged.
Seven outside structures were razed, along with four vehicles. The
damage was estimated at $250,000, said Ms. Dale.
   The cause of the explosion was under investigation, but arson
was ruled out, she added. People were allowed to return to the camp
by 10 p.m.
</TEXT>
