<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--SitkaCrash 1stLd-Writethru a0495 09-06 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Sitka Crash, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0495,0131</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Plane Carrying Players Home from Softball Tournament Crashes in
Alaska</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs 2nd graf to insert Monday time element. Oneil is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SITKA, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A plane carrying softball players home from
a weekend tournament crashed shortly after takeoff, killing one
person and injuring nine others, officials said.
   The plane appeared to have made a forced landing Monday in a
small icefield near Indigo Lake, about five miles southeast of
Sitka, police Officer Dan Bierman said.
   Bierman identified the dead man as Steven K. Oneil, 35. Two
others were seriously injured.
   The cause of the crash was not immediately determined, and
Federal Aviation Administration officials were to investigate the
crash site today, Bierman said.
   Rainy weather may have been a factor, he said.
</TEXT>
