<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-Hailstorm     09-06 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Hailstorm,0131</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hailstorm Injures 2,000 in China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hailstones the size of goose eggs injured more
than 2,000 people and damaged 8,500 acres of cropland in northern
China's Hebei province, an official report said Tuesday.
   The hailstorm in Cangzhou county came so suddenly Saturday
afternoon that pedestrians were caught in the streets and people
inside did not have time to shut the windows, the Economic Daily
said.
   About six inches of hail fell in an outlying district of
Cangzhou, with lesser amounts recorded in the county's city, towns
and villages, it said.
   China has suffered many natural disasters this year, including
severe flooding in the northeast, coastal and southern provinces;
drought in the central provinces; and storms and typhoons in the
south and along the coast.
</TEXT>
