<HEAD>Hydraulic System Fails, But Plane Lands Safely</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hydraulic system on a Continental Airlines
jetliner failed in flight, forcing the crew to lower the landing
gear by hand, but the plane landed safely with 283 people aboard,
authorities said Tuesday.
   Continental Flight 475, an Airbus A-300 from Houston, landed at
8:46 p.m. Monday at Los Angeles International Airport, said Federal
Aviation Administration spokesman Fred O'Donnell. The pilot had
radioed that the system that lowers the landing gear had failed.
   ``Basically they had to mechanically extend the landing gear,''
O'Donnell said. ``It landed without incident and taxied off the
runway.''
