<HEAD>People in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Maureen O'Connor has gained some new
understanding of the hundreds of homeless in the nation's
seventh-largest city.
   For 48 hours, she was one of them.
   O'Connor, 41, wife of Robert O. Peterson, millionaire founder of
Jack in the Box restaurants, spent two days and nights over the
Labor Day weekend living the life of a transient.
   The mayor was rousted from resting spots, watched drug dealers
do business, witnessed gay prostitutes luring clients into bushes,
spent a night in a park, and sought help from government agencies.
   ``It was a lifetime in 48 hours. No one could ever put into a
memo what I have learned,'' said O'Conner, who was nursing swollen
feet Sunday.
   Only three people recognized her _ two homeless women and a
longtime friend.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
