<TEXT>
   The new security system at the South Dakota
State Fair worked. Just ask Gov. George Mickelson.
   The state hired a Nebraska security company for this year's
fair, prompting some criticism from people who think the jobs
should be filled by state residents.
   When Mickelson went to the fair over the weekend, he showed gate
officials the parking sticker on his car, thinking it would gain
him admission.
   The security guard said if he wanted to get in, he'd still have
to pay an entrance fee.
   ``I told her I was the governor, and she said, `I don't care who
you are,''' Mickelson said.
   He said he was glad to pay for the ticket. ``I gave her a $100
bill, and she had change,'' Mickelson said.
