   Grant says she'll promote Habitat for Humanity International
during a 58-city tour the rest of the year.
   The anti-poverty group sells homes at cost to needy people and
charges no interest on its loans that are repaid over 15 to 25
years.
   Ms. Grant sang a No. 1 duet, ``Next Time I Fall,'' in 1986 with
ex-Chicago lead singer Peter Cetera. Her ``Unguarded'' and ``Age to
Age'' albums have sold more than 1 million copies apiece.
