<HEAD>President Cut Clearing Brush</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: INSERTS 1 graf after lead to UPDATE with Reagan comment.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HASTINGS, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan was sporting a small
adhesive bandage on his right arm Tuesday, the result of a minor
mishap while performing chores on his California ranch.
   Reagan, during a stop in Nebraska as he traveled back to
Washington from California, was asked by reporters what had
happened and replied: ``chopping wood.''
   Asked by reporters traveling with Reagan aboard Air Force One
about the bandage, White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said that
``while clearing wood yesterday (Monday) afternoon a small branch
punctured the president's skin on the inside of his right wrist.''
   Fitzwater said the injury required no stitches.
