<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Graham,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Billy Graham Hospitalized For Foot Infection</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Evangelist Billy Graham has been
hospitalized with a foot infection probably caused by a spider
bite, officials of his ministry said Tuesday.
   The 69-year-old evangelist, in western New York for a weeklong
crusade, was admitted to Rochester's Highland Hospital on Labor Day
and was told by doctors he must stay at least two days, said Graham
spokesman A. Larry Ross.
   ``He does have significant pain and swelling in his left foot
but it's a localized infection and doctors have assured him he will
be able to complete his schedule,'' Ross said.
   Ross said a doctor who examined Graham in North Carolina
theorized the evangelist had been bitten by a Brown Recluse spider.
Graham lives in a wooded area of the southern Appalachian Mountains.
   Graham is scheduled to begin an eight-day series of meetings in
Rochester on Sept. 11.
</TEXT>
