<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A scandal involving citizens paying thousands
of dollars to avoid military service has shaken Israel, where the
army is considered a sacred institution and most believe their
nation is surrounded by Arab enemies.
   The story of Israelis paying up to $10,000 in bribes to avoid
serving has been front-page news and dominated radio broadcasts
Tuesday.
   ``Shock waves swept through the IDF (Israeli Defense Force, or
