<HEAD>Nissan Motor to Produce Forklifts in United States</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nissan Motor Co. said Tuesday it will produce
engine-powered forklifts in the United States beginning in October.
   A Nissan Motor official, who spoke on condition of anonymity,
said Nissan and other Japanese groups have purchased Barrett
Industrial Trucks Inc., which has been producing 2,000 folklifts a
year in Marengo in the suburbs of Chicago.
   She said Barrett Industrial Trucks Inc. will produce 4,000 of
Nissan's engine-powered forklifts a year by the end of 1989 at a
remodeled plant in Marengo.
   Last year, Nissan exported 4,000 engine-powered forklifts and
1,000 battery-powered forklifts to the United States, the official
said.
   All of the 180 workers at Barrett Industrial Trucks Inc. will be
retained under the new management, the official said.
   The U.S. company is now owned 20 percent by Nissan Motor, 50
percent by Nissan's wholly owned U.S. Nissan Industrial Equipment
Corp. and 30 percent by the Marubeni group of Japan.
</TEXT>
