<HEAD>Steel Output Rose 3.6 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.918 million tons in
the week ended Sept. 3, an increase of 3.6 percent from the
previous week's 1.851 million tons, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Tuesday.
   The industry's production amounted to 89.9 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 86.8 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
67.723 million net tons, a rise of of 18.5 percent from the 57.137
million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.6 percent of capacity,
compared with 75.7 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Sept. 3: Northeast
Coast, 259,000; Pittsburgh, 203,000; Youngstown, 96,000; Lake Erie,
151,000; Detroit, 167,000; Chicago, 531,000; Midwest, 206,000;
Southern, 214,000; and Western, 91,000.
